$interpreted: Young Man: Golemwalt~ where are you? Golemwalt?
Young Man: Ah...! Y-You must be Golemwalt, right?
Golemwalt: Grrrouuu~?
Walt: You smell something familiar? Maybe it's my mother?
Golemwalt: Grrrooouuu~
Walt: You want to know where my mother is? Sorry, she's...
Golemwalt: Grrrooouuu~
Dagger: Damn human, what are you doing in Totemtaff!?
Dagger: A golem protecting a human? What's going on?
Crushfang: I remember something similar, about ten years ago... Who are you?
Walt: My name is Walt. I'm here to return this to Golemwalt.
Crushfang: Walt? Aren't you the child of that human female from long ago?
Walt: Yes. My mother had always wanted to visit Golemwalt someday and return this gem to him.
Crushfang: I remember... this was his gift to her.
Walt: Mother sold the crystal and made a fortune. It took all that money to cure my disease.
Walt: Afterwards, we worked hard so we could buy it back one day, and return it to Golemwalt.
Dagger: Humans are never this kind... Must be some kind of scheme!
Walt: It's not a scheme... My mother told me she doesn't deserve to hold on to it. Her crimes are too great...
Walt: But If you want to know what I'm really up to, well...
Walt: ...Really, I just wanted to meet my savior. Golemwalt.
Golemwalt: Grrrouuu~?
Walt: My mother? She is resting at home. She's too old now to journey all the way here.
Walt: But she wanted me to tell you that she misses you very much.
Golemwalt: Grrrooouuu!
Crushfang: Well, since you delivered what you came for, I suggest you leave. Totemtaff is not exactly a safe place for humans.
Dagger: Chieftain Crushfang!
Walt: I understand. Thank you.
Golemwalt: Grrrouuu~
Walt: Farewell, Golemwalt. You saved me, buddy.
Golemwalt: Grrrrrrooooouuuuu~
Dagger: Chieftain Crushfang, what was that all about?
Crushfang: It's a story from long, long ago. Care to listen?
